	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>MMC5 Bank Init Problem</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I am working on a SMB1 (using SMBDIS) hack that uses MMC5, But the problem is that the banks are always initilized as fixed 8k bank instead of letting me choose from any other MMC5 bank method. 
<br />
<br />And the worst of it is that $8000-$9fff, $a000-$bfff, and $c000-$dfff is mirroring $e000-$ffff which is a fixed bank!
<br />
<br />Is it the emulator(s)? I dunno, I just need a solution.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Bregalad</b> [ Fri May 01, 2009 1:08 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />By default the MMC5 swaps the last 8k of PRG ROM at $8000, $a000, $c000 and $e000. From there you have to make some code to configure your bankswitching sheme yourself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
